ADDITIONAL NOTICE — DATA-DELETION SOFTWARE, READ BEFORE USE

Reclaim scans your filesystem and, when you apply a batch, moves or
permanently deletes files it identifies as clutter. Some categories are
configured for permanent deletion with no recovery mechanism other than
rebuilding the affected artifact yourself (see the project's ADR-0001 and the
in-app category descriptions). Automated file-deletion software can act on a
misdetection, an unmodeled environment, or a configuration you did not intend.

TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY APPLICABLE LAW:

1. THE AUTHOR PROVIDES NO WARRANTY THAT THIS SOFTWARE WILL CORRECTLY IDENTIFY,
   CLASSIFY, OR SAFELY HANDLE ANY FILE ON YOUR SYSTEM.
2. THE AUTHOR IS NOT LIABLE FOR ANY DATA LOSS, CORRUPTION, DOWNTIME, OR OTHER
   DAMAGE — DIRECT, INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, OR CONSEQUENTIAL — ARISING FROM YOUR
   USE OF THIS SOFTWARE, INCLUDING USE IN "POWER MODE" OR ANY MODE THAT
   PERMITS PERMANENT DELETION.
3. YOU ARE RESPONSIBLE FOR MAINTAINING YOUR OWN BACKUPS BEFORE RUNNING THIS
   SOFTWARE, ESPECIALLY BEFORE ENABLING ANY MODE OR CATEGORY THAT PERMITS
   PERMANENT, UNRECOVERABLE DELETION.
4. This software defaults to a safe mode (Recycle-Bin-only, review-only
   candidate generation, and a restricted category set) on every fresh
   install. Switching out of safe mode is an explicit, typed, logged action
   you take at your own risk — see the in-app first-run notice and
   `docs/architecture/adr/0023-stage2-safe-mode-safety-boundary.md`.

If this disclaimer conflicts with the MIT License text above on the subject of
warranty or liability, this section governs, as it is more specific to the
nature of this software.
